properties.name: Calabar-Gabon SAFE Corridor (via Gembu-Banyo)
properties.description:
TRULY SAFE overland route from Calabar (Nigeria) to Gabon.
**ACTUALLY avoids Anglophone crisis zone** by using Gembu-Banyo crossing.
Enters Cameroon in Adamawa Region (Francophone, safe).

**Total Distance:** 3035 km
**Estimated Drive Time:** 46 hours

**Nigeria segment:** 1116 km
**Cameroon segment:** 1642 km (all in safe Francophone regions)

## Route Segments:
Calabar → Ikom: ✓ Safe
Ikom → Ogoja: ✓ Safe
Ogoja → Wukari: ✓ Safe
Wukari → Jalingo: ✓ Safe
Jalingo → Serti: ✓ Safe
Serti → Gembu: ✓ Safe
Gembu → Mayo Darlé Border: ⚡ CAUTION
Mayo Darlé Border → Banyo: ✓ Safe
Banyo → Tibati: ✓ Safe
Tibati → Ngaoundéré: ✓ Safe
Ngaoundéré → Meiganga: ✓ Safe
Meiganga → Garoua-Boulaï: ✓ Safe
Garoua-Boulaï → Bertoua: ✓ Safe
Bertoua → Ayos: ✓ Safe
Ayos → Yaoundé: ✓ Safe
Yaoundé → Mbalmayo: ✓ Safe
Mbalmayo → Ebolowa: ✓ Safe
Ebolowa → Ambam: ✓ Safe
Ambam → Kye-Ossi: ⚡ CAUTION
Kye-Ossi → Bitam: ✓ Safe
Bitam → Oyem: ✓ Safe
Oyem → Mitzic: ✓ Safe

## Why This Route:
• **Gembu-Banyo crossing** enters Adamawa Region (Francophone)
• **Zero transit** through Anglophone NW/SW crisis zones
• **Equatorial Guinea** completely avoided

## Trade-offs:
• **Longer route** - goes north through Nigeria first
• **Mambilla Plateau** - rough roads, 4x4 essential, dry season only
• **More Nigeria driving** but on safer roads

## When to Travel:
• **Dry season (Nov-Feb)** essential for Mambilla Plateau
• Road can be impassable in rainy season (Mar-Oct)

properties.name: Calabar
properties.description: Starting point. Nigerian port city.

properties.name: Ikom
properties.description: Head north through Nigeria instead of crossing into Cameroon here.

properties.name: Ogoja
properties.description: Continue north on Nigerian roads.

properties.name: Wukari
properties.description: Taraba State. Route continues toward Mambilla Plateau.

properties.name: Jalingo
properties.description: Capital of Taraba State. Last major city before Mambilla Plateau. Resupply here.

properties.name: Serti
properties.description: Gateway to Mambilla Plateau. Road gets rougher from here.

properties.name: Gembu
properties.description: Mambilla Plateau - highest point in Nigeria (~1800m). Cool climate. Border crossing ahead.

properties.name: Mayo Darlé Border
properties.description: Nigeria-Cameroon border. Small crossing. Have all papers ready. Remote but legitimate.

properties.name: Banyo
properties.description: First major town in Cameroon - ADAMAWA REGION (Francophone). SAFE. Not part of Anglophone crisis.

properties.name: Tibati
properties.description: Safe transit town. Adamawa Region.

properties.name: Ngaoundéré
properties.description: Major city - SAFE. Railway terminus. Good resupply point.

properties.name: Meiganga
properties.description: Safe transit. Adamawa Region.

properties.name: Garoua-Boulaï
properties.description: Border town with CAR (not crossing). Continue south.

properties.name: Bertoua
properties.description: Capital of East Region - SAFE. Major stop.

properties.name: Ayos
properties.description: Safe transit on route to Yaoundé.

properties.name: Yaoundé
properties.description: Capital - SAFE. Rest, resupply, embassies.

properties.name: Mbalmayo
properties.description: South of Yaoundé. Main route south.

properties.name: Ebolowa
properties.description: Capital of South Region - SAFE.

properties.name: Ambam
properties.description: Last Cameroonian town before Gabon border.

properties.name: Kye-Ossi
properties.description: Tripoint border. Take GABON crossing (toward Bitam), NOT Equatorial Guinea.

properties.name: Bitam
properties.description: Welcome to Gabon - SAFE.

properties.name: Oyem
properties.description: Capital of Woleu-Ntem Province. Good resupply.

properties.name: Mitzic
properties.description: Continue south toward Libreville or east toward parks.
